pr_review_body:
The `formatAttributeValue` function handle arrays, urls, number formatting, etc.... We should also handle attribute array too. Removing the "s" to get the main attribute for translation should work in most cases I think... 
In most case this attributes are not displayed because it's filtered with the `extra-filters` property.

```ts
function computeMainAttribute(attribute: string) {
  if (attribute.charAt(attribute.length - 1) === "s") {
    return attribute.slice(0, -1);
  }
  return attribute;
}
```

```ts
  if (Array.isArray(attributeValue)) {
    const mainAttribute = computeMainAttribute(attribute);
    return attributeValue
      .map((_value) =>
        computeAttributeValueDisplay(
          localize,
          stateObj,
          entities,
          mainAttribute,
          _value
        )
      )
      .join(", ");
  }
  ```

Maybe we can do something like:

```python
if self.df.empty:
    return self.df._default_to_pandas(lambda df: df.loc[key])
```

It's similar to your implementation, but will work on row label objects too I believe

